   205	
   206	Add a deterministic precursor-isolation unit test (NOT gated on corpus): drive the writer (or a small extracted helper around the per-scan commit) through a sequence where an MS1 parent scan FAILS after its filterKey/precursor-map point, followed by another MS1 parent and an MSn child whose filter prefix matches the failed parent. Assert the child does NOT resolve its precursor_index through the skipped scan (it resolves to the later valid parent, or precursor_index is null), AND ordinals stay dense AND facet/metadata parity holds. If forcing a failure at the exact precursor-map line requires a seam, extract the commit logic into a small testable method rather than depending on a real RAW failing at that line.
