   286	<risks>
   287	- **Primary: streaming refactor regressing v1 conformance.** The move from full-facet accumulation to incremental row groups must preserve index/multiset/footer-KV/cv_list invariants. Mitigation: schemas, point layout, footer KV strings, and chrom-data CURIE registration are reused verbatim (shared helper, S4); final KV set via CloseAsync after all row groups (S1); identical-multiset + parity + cv_list + full-suite tests gate every change (Tasks 2,4).
   288	- **Footer KV timing (S1).** spectrum_count / point counts / chromatogram_tic_source are unknown at open; if set at OpenAsync they would be wrong/zero. Mitigation: CloseAsync(finalMetadata) sets them after the last row group, before dispose; FinalMetadataSetAfterRowGroups test proves the footer round-trips.
   289	- **Precursor-map poisoning (S2).** _precursorScanNumbers is shared parent-resolution state; a pre-commit mutation survives a failed scan. Mitigation: moved into the success-only commit block; deterministic precursor-isolation unit test.
   290	- **The silent-buffer trap.** A non-seekable sink buffers the whole facet in RAM with no error. Mitigation: OpenAsync asserts CanSeek; data facets only ever target temp FileStreams; NonSeekableSinkRejected test (Task 1); warning sign = RSS scaling with file size despite "streaming" / zero temp files on disk (Task 4 RSS measurement catches it).
   291	- **Buffer sizing with three open facets (RESEARCH A2).** 3 x 1M-row buffers ~= tens of MB; if too large, lower the RowGroupRowCap default (one field). Caught at Task 4 measurement.
   292	- **Corpus availability.** MEM-02 / ROB gates depend on the large files being present; verified present today (954 MB, 418 MB, 8.4 GB). The robustness NUnit test self-ignores off-corpus so the suite stays green elsewhere.
   293	- **Exact S4 throw line unconfirmed (RESEARCH A1).** The all-or-nothing staging is correct whether the throw is before or after the old append; the S2 fix (precursor-map in commit block) makes the skip safe regardless. Low risk.
